    "Project Highlight",
    "Each of our projects present a unique solution to managing daylight. Explore a detailed look at some of our key projects to see how Veil can add value to your project.",
    "Catalyst",
    "Omaha, NECatalyst represents a true commitment to the concept of adaptive reuse. The Omaha Steel Works building - originally built in 1906 - went through a multi-year complete renovation to be reborn as an extraordinary co-working and incubation space adjacent to the University of Nebraska Medicine campus in Omaha, NE. Veil partnered to deliver a carefully coordinated Draper motorized and manual roller shade system in the primary build-out of the facility, as well as subsequent tenant buildouts. Architect: APMAEngineer: Morrissey EngineeringGeneral Contractor: Boyd Jones Construction",
    "​",
    "© 2025 by Veil | engineered shading."
